- The "no-mani mani" as a 2026 trend category — barely covered as a deliberate choice
- Pearl chrome and opalescent shades as a distinct category from standard shimmer
- Color coordination with jewelry metal tones (gold vs platinum vs rose gold settings)
- Muted/dusty non-white options (sage green, dusty rose, lavender, terracotta) — under-served for non-traditional brides

Audience Blind Spots:
- Darker skin tones — competitors either ignore them or offer one generic "any nude works" line
- Brides with warm/olive undertones — cool-pink suggestions dominate editorial but are actively wrong for them
- First-time nail color decision-makers — overwhelmed by too many options with no framework

Our Strategic Approach:
Differentiation: Build the post around three decision variables (dress undertone, skin undertone, lighting) and give a clear framework before presenting color options. Lead with photography performance as the primary lens — not just aesthetics. Include a decision matrix. Cover the 2026 shift toward muted, dusty, pearlescent options as a distinct category.
Structure Plan: Framework first, then colour-by-colour with skin tone notes and photo performance guidance built into each section. End with the 2026 palette and a coordination guide for ring metal tones.
Tone Direction: Informed, warm editorial voice — like a beauty editor who also understands photography.

